PrecisAmendment to the FOOD AND DRUG REGULATIONS (Schedule No. 870) permitting the use of a new source of chymosin B, produced by a modified strain of Aspergillus niger, which is one of the principal active ingredient in calf rennet, the enzyme preparation used to coagulate milk in the preparation of cheese and other dairy products.
